The paper deals with Named Entity Recognition (NER) in Twitter, which is a task related to natural language processing (NLP) and information retrieval (IR), suggesting cs.CL and cs.IR as likely sub-categories. The proposed approach uses features extracted from both images and text, indicating a possible connection to computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Finally, the paper proposes a novel architecture that does not rely on hand-crafted features or domain-specific knowledge, suggesting a possible connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category.
